  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and dice finely</p><p>Trim the ends off your <strong>Brussels sprouts</strong>, then chop in half lengthways</p><p>Chop your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> into thirds</p><p>Peel and chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1666001209183-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1666001209183-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1666001209183-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1666001209183-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1666001209183-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced leek </strong>to the pan with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook, covered, for 6-7 min or until softened</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1666001212488-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1666001212488-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1666001212488-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1666001212488-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1666001212488-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the leek has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for a further 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, remove the pan from the heat and add the <strong>chopped Brussels sprouts </strong>and<strong> chopped Tenderstem broccoli</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – these are your <strong>green veggies</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1666001217926-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
