      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat 3 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [4 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> in a pot over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[4 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Gradually whisk 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[525ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> into the roux, a little at a time, and cook for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains – this is your <strong>béchamel sauce</strong></p>",
